  "market_context": "Tesla was in an uptrend; the analyst highlighted a recently completed inverse head and shoulders pattern on the daily chart, followed by a strong impulsive move upward.",
  "key_observation": "The Auto Chart Pattern Indicator automatically identified an inverse head and shoulders pattern with left shoulder at ~175.0, head at ~165.0, right shoulder at ~170.0, and a breakout that quickly reached the indicator’s projected target near 249.2–249.7.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: The analyst introduced the 'Auto Chart Pattern Indicator' and noted it automatically detects chart patterns including inverse head and shoulders.",
    "Step 2: He switched to TSLA on the daily timeframe and applied the indicator, selecting all patterns and enabling price targets.",
    "Step 3: He pointed to the specific inverse head and shoulders pattern, identifying the left shoulder (~175.0), head (~165.0), and right shoulder (~170.0) from the chart annotations.",
    "Step 4: He observed the neckline break and highlighted that the indicator generated an automatic target level near 249.2–249.7.",
    "Step 5: He confirmed the target was reached very quickly after the breakout, demonstrating the pattern’s effectiveness in this instance."
  ],
  "outcome": "The price broke out of the inverse head and shoulders pattern and reached the indicator’s automatic target (≈249.2–249.7) rapidly, confirming the bullish signal.",
  "lessons": "Automated chart pattern indicators can reliably identify classic reversal patterns like inverse head and shoulders and project accurate targets—especially when combined with trend context—but should be used alongside other confluence factors for higher probability setups.",
